# VLink License Notices

This distribution of VLink (v@VLINK_VERSION@) statically links and/or bundles
third-party software. The full license text of every component actually
shipped in *this* build is provided in subdirectories alongside this file.

VLink itself is licensed under Apache License, Version 2.0; see `vlink/LICENSE`.

The table below is the **superset** of libraries VLink may bundle across all
build configurations. The set actually shipped in your install is the set of
subdirectories present under this `licenses/` directory — entries listed here
without a matching subdirectory have not been bundled (typically because they
were resolved against a system package manager, which ships its own license
files).

| Library | License | Homepage | How it ships in this build |
|---------|---------|----------|----------------------------|
| `vlink` | Apache-2.0 | <https://vlink.work> | primary project |
| `lzav` | MIT | <https://github.com/avaneev/lzav> | header-only, linked into libvlink |
| `mcap` | MIT | <https://github.com/foxglove/mcap> | header-only, linked into libvlink |
| `json` | MIT | <https://github.com/nlohmann/json> | header-only, linked into libvlink and CLIs |
| `spdlog` | MIT | <https://github.com/gabime/spdlog> | header-only, default log backend |
| `quill` | MIT | <https://github.com/odygrd/quill> | header-only, optional log backend |
| `argparse` | MIT | <https://github.com/p-ranav/argparse> | header-only, linked into CLI binaries |
| `bitsery` | MIT | <https://github.com/fraillt/bitsery> | header-only, linked into proxy binaries |
| `exprtk` | MIT | <https://www.partow.net/programming/exprtk/> | header-only, linked into dump/viewer/webviz |
| `websocketpp` | BSD-3-Clause | <https://github.com/zaphoyd/websocketpp> | header-only, linked into vlink-foxglove |
| `asio` | BSL-1.0 | <https://think-async.com/Asio/> | header-only, linked into vlink-foxglove |
| `eigen3` | MPL-2.0 | <https://eigen.tuxfamily.org> | header-only, linked into vlink-viewer (MPL-2.0 subset only — see below) |
| `tinyxml2` | Zlib | <https://github.com/leethomason/tinyxml2> | static, linked into libvlink-* (CPM) |
| `cpptoml` | MIT | <https://github.com/skystrife/cpptoml> | static, linked into libvlink-* (CPM) |
| `foonathan_memory` | Zlib | <https://github.com/foonathan/memory> | static, linked via Fast-DDS (CPM) |
| `fastcdr` | Apache-2.0 | <https://github.com/eProsima/Fast-CDR> | static, linked via Fast-DDS (CPM) |
| `fastdds` | Apache-2.0 | <https://github.com/eProsima/Fast-DDS> | static, linked into libvlink-dds (CPM, patched) |
| `cyclonedds` | EPL-2.0 OR EDL-1.0 | <https://github.com/eclipse-cyclonedds/cyclonedds> | static, linked into libvlink-ddsc (CPM, patched) |
| `iceoryx` | Apache-2.0 | <https://github.com/eclipse-iceoryx/iceoryx> | static, linked into libvlink-shm; iox-roudi binary (CPM, patched) |
| `protobuf` | BSD-3-Clause | <https://github.com/protocolbuffers/protobuf> | static, linked into CLI/viewer/webviz (CPM) |
| `flatbuffers` | Apache-2.0 | <https://github.com/google/flatbuffers> | static, linked into CLI/viewer/webviz (CPM) |
| `sqlite3` | Public Domain | <https://www.sqlite.org> | static, linked into libvlink (CPM) |
| `openssl` | Apache-2.0 | <https://www.openssl.org> | static, linked into libvlink for security (CPM) |
| `zstd` | BSD-3-Clause | <https://github.com/facebook/zstd> | static (library only, BSD-3); the upstream `COPYING` file (GPL-2.0, for the CLI we do not ship) is intentionally not bundled |
| `ffmpeg` | LGPL-2.1-or-later | <https://ffmpeg.org> | dynamic, bundled by build-conan.sh (viewer) |
| `qt` | LGPL-3.0 | <https://www.qt.io> | dynamic, bundled by build-conan.sh (viewer) |
| `osg` | OSGPL-0.0 | <https://www.openscenegraph.com> | dynamic, bundled by build-conan.sh (viewer) |
| `icu` | Unicode-DFS-2016 | <https://icu.unicode.org> | dynamic, bundled by build-conan.sh (Qt dep) |

## Notes on copyleft-licensed components

### Eigen MPL-2.0-only

The Eigen headers ship a small subset of files licensed under LGPL or, very
rarely, GPL. VLink does not use those modules, so only `COPYING.MPL2` and
`COPYING.README` are shipped here. To audit, build with
`-DCMAKE_CXX_FLAGS=-DEIGEN_MPL2_ONLY` and verify there are no compile errors
in the viewer code path.

### Cyclone DDS EPL-2.0

`libvlink-ddsc` statically links Cyclone DDS (EPL-2.0 OR EDL-1.0). The
corresponding source for the static-linked binary is available at the upstream
URL above plus the patch documented in `cyclonedds/MODIFICATIONS.md` (when
present in this install).

### LGPL re-linkability for Conan-bundled libs

`ffmpeg`, `qt`, `osg`, and `icu` are bundled as separate dynamic libraries
(`.so` / `.dylib` / `.framework`) in `lib/`. LGPL §6 is satisfied by this
shape: users may replace each of those library files with their own
LGPL-compatible build of the same SONAME without modifying the rest of the
vlink distribution.

## How to verify which libraries are present

```sh
ls "<install-prefix>/@VLINK_LICENSES_DIR@/"
```
